The most awaited week of my life in HCK

Introduction:

I hope the week has been great for all! I'm Dilasha pradhan from kathmandu. Now I am a student of Wolverhampton university(Herald college).

Day 1 (Module: Academic skills and team-based learning)

The new journey of my bachelor started with a cold thursday morning. I was very excited for my first day of college, as it was the new beginning step towards my career. I was so thrilled for this day that i couldn't even sleep the night before. I was also kind of nervous because the environment was new to me and i was going to meet new people and learn so many stuffs.

My day started with a good breakfast and I also wished to have a day as my breakfast. My first class started from 9:30 am so I reached collage at sharp 9am. When I entered the gate I got a call from my friend. After that we both when to reception to sign the contract . Then we headed towards our class. When we reached our class the lecture was already started. We quickly got seated, there was a girl next to us . We interacted with each other, she was very polite. After some time the teacher introduced himself followed by other faculty of our module. In the introduction session the teacher pointed the girl seating next to us .The girl stood up and introduced herself which amazed us because we thought she was freshers as well but turns out she is one of the graduate from wolverhampton University who will be there to help us with our module.

After some time the class was about to get over and we were kind of bored sitting for 2 hr 30 min maybe because it was my new experience. In the class hour i got to about the university and how the system works. I was pleased to hear that all information and also got a little bit as it was new to me. tried my best understand the difference. After 5 min class got over.

DAY 2 (Module: fundamental of computing, Academic skills and team-based learning)

Second day started with a little nervousness and full of excitement. I worked up and made a glass of coffee for me. I had 2 classes which was both for 2hrs 30 min. My class was scheduled at 12:00 pm so i reached the college 10 min prior. I waited for my friend for 2-3 min then we headed towards the class.

We had our lecture for web technologies from 12:00pm - 2:00pm which was fun as well as i got to learn about blog and how we should write it. After a long lecture we had a 1 hour break in which me and my friends played basketball for an hour and we went to have a stick food which is near our college. After that we still had an hour left so we decided to sit in student lounge and chat until our tutorial.

At 3:20 we headed towards our tutorial class where we got to learn how to login in the classroom, blog tools and other software needed for our session. Then we practically learned about blog and how it is done. Our tutorial class got over at 5:00 pm. We were very exhausted as it was a very long day. So we headed towards our home. After a quick 15 min walk i reached my home and jumped into my bed and got some rest.

﻿

Day 3(Module: Fundamental of computing, introductory programming and problems sol..)

On wednesday, I worked up around at 7am as i didn't had a morning class . I slowly then got freshen up and had my breakfast at 8 am and i started getting ready for the day as i had 2 workshop for the day.

I reached college at around 9:20am, we had our class at 9:30 am to 12:00pm. we had a workshop for "Fundamental of Computer" which was very useful and helpful for me. That class was very helpful if i was late or i couldn't attend that l class it would have been a big loss for me. After 2 hrs 30 min the class was finished and we headed out and went straight to library and started to do our own pending works. We had 1 hrs break and in that time we did some of our assignments.

Our second workshop was of "introductory programming and problems sol.." i had no idea what was going happen because we hadn't have lecture class of this workshop. So, me and my friend head to our class with no idea. Class started teacher tough us very useful stuff of programming that was my first time I enjoyed doing programming. I didn't even realized the time and the workshop class was finished. After class we head to our home.

Day 4 (Module: Academic skills and team-based learning,introductory programming and problem sol..)

Fourth day started i was little tired but i waked up saw the routine and i had 2 lecture classes. I quickly started to get ready for my day and wished to have a great day. My class was at 9: 30am to 11:30am. I got college at 9:00 am there was time left for the class so we played basketball with my friend for half and hrs.

While playing we didn't notice the time so we were late for the first lecture class. So I ran out for class thankfully I reach to my class before teacher. The first lecture was of "introductory programming and problem sol.." This was the lecture class of that day when I enjoyed doing the programming. Just like the workshop class this class also helped.

After first lecture class we had second class to but between that we had 30 min break. In that break me and my friends roamed around in college. Blink the time flew and second class started. I had lecture class of"Academic skills and team-based learning" i learned new things from this module but some point there was things that i didn't understand that's way I noted the topic so I will ask the question on tutorial or workshop class. After a long class we head to our own house. When I reached my home I got fresh and ate and jumped in to mt bed to have some rest.

Day 5 (Module:Fundamental of computing, Academic skill and team-based learning)

My day started with fresh morning i wake up at 6am cause fridays class was shift to 7 am so it was my first early morning class. I was half awake because the day before i slept late watching football match. It was so cold at morning my hand, nose was cold as ice.

I reached college at 6:55 am my friend was already there waiting for me. After that we went straight to our class. First class was of lecture fundamental of computing. Our class started a little late but it was fun studying early morning because studying at morning brain can concentrate and also easy to understand. The class finished 9:00 am and our second class was at 3:30 pm so we had 6 hrs left it means the whole day.

Then we decided to go our home but my friends house was near. So, we went to her house and have lunch and also had fun. We had so much fun that we didn't even realized the time we spent at her house. Then we all left for our second class. We reached 5 min late that's way our teacher allow us to enter the class. It was our tutorial class of" Academic skills and team-based learning ". At this tutorial we learned how to mail if we need leave or have any problem then where to mail and whom to mail. And also manage the settings of our college mails. It was very useful full and helpful. Then our class got over at 5:00pm. I was so exhausted as it was such a long day. I went to home and straight started to write my pending blog.

Conclusion:

Week 1 in HCK was unexpectedly very friendly and was knowledge full of experience. This week module was easy to understand and was very useful for our upcoming course to.That I had so much fun and gain so much knowledge in one week that I didn't even expected from myself. Hope the same energy will come for upcoming weeks. Thank You !!!!

﻿
